<br>
I'll start with a comparison to the most popular group (in my opinion)<br>
<br>
Cleric, Enchanter, Warrior. <br>
Happy go luck group right?.<br>
<br>
Now let say a Warrior is not avail and toss mage in the mix.  <br>
<br>
Cleric, Enchanter, Mage /pet to tank. <br>
The Pet is going to out dmg this group and the group will loose exp on a regular basis.  This is very unrewarding.  Enchanters and clerics do not normally nuke.  After dmg shield buffs and rods mages can be to low on mana to nuke enough.<br>
<br>
Add a Rogue or warrior of similar lvl to the pet and (not twinked) and i can asure you the pet will out dmg them most of the time.  How can i say this?  the pet is going to be way more efficiant unless hes is not buffed or given the rear of the opponent for rear attack advantage. of course after lvl 50 this is less likely but still very possible with lower lvl melees.  <br>
<br>
Telling the masses to cripple their pets to asure exp is lame.<br>
<br>
You might say that the people of this group can out nuke the pet?  well mana does not come cheap and if they dont want to have to stop and med after each fight each caster is going to stick to their specialty.  Sure the mage might out nuke his pet when mana allows.    <br>
<br>
No matter how you look at it this pet exp thing is going to be the Bane of All pet classes,  it stinks foul and whether or not players out dmg a pet it will still be negative association.  It is going to go against pet dependant classes whether it be fact or ignorance. <br>
<br>
Lets look at this.  Pet classes are offensive melee classes (some more than others).  If you interchange any of the pet classes with a pure melee class you avoid the pet exp issue.  <br>
<br>
The other delima is weather or not the players can trust the system to determine when they do and dont get full exp.  <br>
<br>
The quote about pets and exp is contradiciton in its worst.   its says if group out dmgs pet then it says if any one individual out dmgs pet.  <br>
<br>
There is a huge differance.  Now the players have to wonder (And if they dont want to be bothered with wondering they dont allow pets and or pet classes)is the computer taking short cuts in this calculation is it going to pool multiple pet dmg against the player/s???<br>
is it pc group vs pets group or is it highest ranking pc vs highest ranking pet. <br>
Or <br>
or <br>
or <br>
I'd rather play than be bothered so i'll illiminate pets from my game.<br>
<br>
get my message?<br>
<br>
Also this exp while soloing thing is a pure nagg,  talk about hasseling the player.  Gee now we have a bunch of pet classes constantly killing their pet and resummoning.  All it does is make players go through huge efforts to avoid exp penalties.  And in doing so they sacrafice several spellines of summoned gear that they finaly found a use for on their pets.  <br>
<br>
And what exactly is wrong with a bunch of pet classes getting together to send thier pets out and destroy targets?  As unpopular pet classes are becoming, its one of the few options we have left for grouping.  All the players i know that run a pet class as their primary, all swear by the joy they found in grouping togeather.  And no matter what you say it was their last option not their first.  I usually end up in a pet only group after long hours of LFG dispare.  but i'll admitt the pet only groups are becoming more common, and i'm starting to long for them.  geee i wonder why?<br>
<br>
